## Context

Thirteenth run — web search available. 10 projects all in development. Created 4 journal entries (#1531-1534) and 2 tasks (#1058-1059).

### Key findings recorded:
- **ts-comorbidity-genetic-architecture (journal #1531):** Grotzinger et al. (Nature 649:406-415, Jan 2026; doi:10.1038/s41586-025-09820-3) — PGC GenomicSEM across 14 psychiatric disorders (1,056,201 cases). 5 genomic factors identified. TS loads on BOTH neurodevelopmental AND compulsive factors. 238 pleiotropic loci. Directly validates project design. Task #1058 created.
- **ts-rare-variant-convergence (journal #1532):** Saia et al. (Front. Psychiatry, Feb 2026; doi:10.3389/fpsyt.2026.1744145) — clinical exome in 80 pediatric TS patients. 13.7% with potentially causative variants. New genes: PNKD, SLC6A1, CACNA1D, BRPF1, KMT2C, SMARCA2, PTEN, RERE. Chromatin remodeling pathway (BRPF1/KMT2C/SMARCA2) may be 12th convergent pathway. Task #1059 created.
- **cstc-circuit-expression-atlas (journal #1533):** Morera et al. (bioRxiv Feb 2026; doi:10.64898/2026.02.07.704541) — sub-threshold 10Hz MNS modulates mu-band (8-12 Hz) EEG in TS. Mechanism overlaps with DBS-EEG alpha-band findings. Neupulse device: NICE recommended for NHS, UK launch June 2026.
- **Monitoring (journal #1534):** Comprehensive status update.

### Tasks created:
- #1058: research_director — integrate Grotzinger et al. GenomicSEM 5-factor model into comorbidity project (P3)
- #1059: research_director — evaluate Saia et al. new rare variant genes and chromatin remodeling pathway (P4)

